in-bottom:0px;">Hi, and welcome back to Line Sheet. Today, <strong>Rachel S=
trugatz</strong>
digs into what=E2=80=99s really happening at Glossier, the beauty brand (or=
 maybe just <em>the</em> brand?) of our time. Up top, some C-suite news fro=
m Saks Global, and my final thoughts on the final New York shows. <br/><br/=
></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I=E2=80=99ve had a fabulous p=
ast 24 hours here. Yesterday afternoon, I wore a hard hat to walk through t=
he new <strong>Laura Gonzalez</strong>=E2=80=93designed Printemps departmen=
t store at 1 Wall Street, set to open this spring, just a block away from
Puck=E2=80=99s South Tribeca headquarters. More soon, but all I have to say=
 for now is: Holy cow. It=E2=80=99s lavish, it=E2=80=99s inventive, it=E2=
=80=99s fun=E2=80=94this is going to be a <em>thing</em>. Thanks to the ret=
ailer=E2=80=99s amazing U.S. C.E.O., <strong>Laura Lendrum</strong>, for ta=
king the time. <br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">After=
 Thom Browne, I headed up to Majorelle, on 63rd Street, for a dinner in hon=
or of designer <strong>Victor Glemaud</strong>=E2=80=99s collection with Pa=
tterson Flynn. Victor has a really
special group of friends=E2=80=94including <strong>Bethann Hardison</strong=
>, <strong>Kate Young</strong>, <strong>Virginia Smith</strong>, and <stron=
g>Patrick Robinson</strong>=E2=80=94and I couldn=E2=80=99t think of a bette=
r way to end this New York Fashion Week. (We mostly talked about our depend=
ence on The RealReal, not the shows.) <br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;ma=
rgin-bottom:0px;">At Victor=E2=80=99s dinner, I sat with Line Sheet reader =
<strong>Lisa Metcalfe</strong>, a longtime business consultant to fashion b=
rands of
various stages and sizes. After walking the Bergdorf Goodman floor the othe=
r day, she came to the conclusion that Phoebe Philo is the best thing going=
, both in terms of design and quality. The next morning, I stopped by Luisa=
viaroma on Bond Street to try on pieces from Philo=E2=80=99s Collection B. =
(It=E2=80=99s good.)<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
By the time you read this, I=E2=80=99ll be at the Oscar de la Renta store u=
ptown, where <strong>Laura Kim</strong> and <strong>Fernando Garcia</strong=
>
are showing their Fall/Winter 2025 collection to a group of friends and cli=
ents. No press, except for me. More on that tomorrow=E2=80=94and pray (or w=
hatever you do) that my flight takes off tonight!</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"=
><br/>Mentioned in this issue: Glossier, <strong>Emily Weiss</strong>, Char=
lotte Tilbury, LVMH, Sephora, Rhode, <strong>Hailey Bieber</strong>, <stron=
g>Selena Gomez</strong>, Rare Beauty, <strong>Lady Gaga</strong>, Haus Labs=
, Off-White, <strong>Francesco Ragazzi</strong>, Palm Angels,
Saks, <strong>Jeff Pedersen</strong>, <strong>Mark Weinstein</strong>, Calv=
in Klein, NYFW, <strong>Joseph Altuzarra</strong>, Oscar de la Renta, <stro=
ng>Michael Kors</strong>, <strong>Tory Burch</strong>, <strong>Thom Browne<=
/strong>, and many more=E2=80=A6=C2=A0</p></div>
